dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2145, \"end\": 2158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"score\": 0.9999967356428517, \"rank\": 3.2635946781599414e-06, \"text\": \"Conservatives\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\"}, {\"begin\": 2200, \"end\": 2204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5067736388761457e-17, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the previous legislature\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolute majority\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"the Left\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"the support\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2141}, {\"ngram\": \"a censor motion\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"email\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She highlighted issues including the fact thatNew Popular Front's 178 seats are well short of the 289 needed for a majority and its candidate Castets is likely to be rejected by other parties.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9689613963422207e-14, \"text\": \"Popular Front\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\", \"score\": 0.5009607382045541, \"rank\": 0.6944444444443503, \"text\": \"Castets\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castets_(grape)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"its candidate\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"other parties\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Macron's own politics and allied government have been \\\"widely rejected by the French,\\\" Massoc added, and no party will form an alliance with far-right National Rally.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2421, \"end\": 2427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.338591693658649e-40, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5735532878796636, \"rank\": 0.5535610422472148, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2572, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"allied government\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"Massoc\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"no party\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"an alliance\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even within the leftist grouping, parties are divided and some will refuse any sort of alliance with centrists, she said.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the leftist grouping\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2620}, {\"ngram\": \"parties\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2629}, {\"ngram\": \"any sort\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"alliance\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2683}, {\"ngram\": \"centrists\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One outcome could see the right-wing Les Republicains willing to form a \\\"passive majority\\\" with the center, but the former appears reluctant to lose \\\"what remains of its specificity,\\\" Massoc added, and opposition in parliament would still be high.\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2748, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999761644179, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Les Republicains\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Republicans_(France)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One outcome\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"passive majority\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"its specificity\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"Massoc\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2901}, {\"ngram\": \"opposition\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"parliament\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are further questions over how such a divided parliament will agree on any legislation, with approval of the 2025 budget looming.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"further questions\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 2987}, {\"ngram\": \"such a divided parliament\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3022}, {\"ngram\": \"any legislation\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"approval\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even in 2022, Macronresorted to usinga special constitutional power to pass the next year's spending bill.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Macronresorted\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"special constitutional power\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"the next year's spending bill\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is also likely to be fierce debate over how - or whether - to take action to tackle France'shuge debt pile, and whether flagship Macronist policies such as raising the national retirement age can or should be unwound.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fierce debate\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3283}, {\"ngram\": \"debt pile\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3316}, {\"ngram\": \"flagship Macronist policies\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3357}, {\"ngram\": \"the national retirement age\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the French political system, the parliament has relatively little power and between 2017 and 2022, 65% of texts adopted were laws proposed by the government rather than parliament, Massoc noted.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3439, \"end\": 3445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5735532878796636, \"rank\": 0.5535610422472148, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the parliament\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3478}, {\"ngram\": \"relatively little power\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3506}, {\"ngram\": \"65%\", \"from\": 3534, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"texts\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3546}, {\"ngram\": \"laws\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3564}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3591}, {\"ngram\": \"parliament\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3614}, {\"ngram\": \"Massoc\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From a markets perspective, the FrenchCAC 40index has fallen over 4.5% since theresult of the electionon July 7.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3743, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a markets perspective\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3657}, {\"ngram\": \"the FrenchCAC 40index\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3680}, {\"ngram\": \"theresult\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3717}, {\"ngram\": \"the electionon\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butanalysts saya divided parliament could actually lead to more stability in stocks and bonds as it will likely prevent the implementation of some parties' more populist policies.\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butanalysts\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3755}, {\"ngram\": \"divided parliament\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3779}, {\"ngram\": \"more stability\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3817}, {\"ngram\": \"stocks\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"bonds\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3837}, {\"ngram\": \"the implementation\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3882}, {\"ngram\": \"some parties' more populist policies\", \"from\": 3886, \"to\": 3922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Political parties have their sights set firmly on the 2027 presidential race - which Macron cannot run in - and very few will want to be responsible for cutting public spending in order to tackle the public deficit, Renaud Foucart, senior lecturer in economics at Lancaster University, told CNBC by phone.\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 4230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4010, \"end\": 4016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.338591693658649e-40, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 4148, \"end\": 4155, \"title\": \"h